<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="100" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="100">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="100">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis itoana" order="Diaporthales" pageId="11" pageNumber="100" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="itoana">Melanconis itoana</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Betula ermanii" order="Fagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ermanii">Betula ermanii</taxonomicName>
in Japan (
<bibRefCitation author="Kobayashi, T" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Government Forest Experiment Station" pageId="21" pageNumber="110" pagination="1 - 242" title="Taxonomic studies of Japanese Diaporthaceae with special reference to their life-histories." volume="226" year="1970">Kobayashi 1970</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Fan, XL" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="21" pageNumber="110" url="http://doi.org/10.1007/s11557-016-1163-2" year="2016">Fan et al. (2016)</bibRefCitation>
isolated it from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Betula albosinensis" order="Fagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albosinensis">Betula albosinensis</taxonomicName>
as a new record in China. 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis itoana" order="Diaporthales" pageId="11" pageNumber="100" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="itoana">Melanconis itoana</taxonomicName>
is characterised by fusoid, green-brown alpha conidia with acute ends (13 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) and hyaline, cylindrical or crescent beta conidia (9.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
).
</paragraph>
